oracle.pg.common

Interface DataConverterListener

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ProgressListener

    public interface DataConverterListener
extends ProgressListener
    This interface defines a few core APIs to that can be used to report progress of a data conversion process.

    • Method Detail

      • continueOnError

        boolean continueOnError(long errs,
                        long progress,
                        java.lang.Object offender,
                        java.lang.String mesg)
        Returns true if the data conversion is to be continued upon encountering this error. Data conversion is supposed to be interrupted if this method returns false
        Parameters:
        errs - number of errors encountered so far.
        progress - a long value indicating the current progress. It must be a positive integer.
        offender - the object value that triggers an error condition
        mesg - an optional string value describing the current progress and error condition.
